3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates SHIB/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium index between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange applies a +/-0.375% funding rate cap to prevent extreme payments during high volatility periods. Funding fees are exchanged directly between long and short position holders based on their position size at settlement time."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SHIB","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SHIB's meme coin status creates significant retail sentiment-driven price movements, often resulting in sustained funding rate imbalances on Bitget. The large trading volume and Bitget's fast listing capabilities for trending tokens make SHIB/USDT particularly attractive for funding arbitrageurs seeking consistent rate premiums."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SHIB/USDT on Bitget typically exhibits positive funding rates during meme coin rally periods, with rates often exceeding 0.1% per 8-hour interval during high retail interest phases. The pair shows strong correlation with broader meme coin sector movements and social media sentiment spikes. Negative funding rates are less common but can occur during extended bearish periods or when institutional shorts accumulate positions. Weekend funding rates tend to be more volatile due to reduced institutional arbitrage activity and higher retail participation ratios."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget's SHIB/USDT pair offers consistent arbitrage opportunities due to frequent premium/discount situations relative to other major exchanges. The exchange's copy trading ecosystem can amplify funding rate imbalances as retail traders follow popular strategies en masse. Optimal execution requires monitoring Bitget's order book depth, which can vary significantly during Asian and European trading hours. Cross-exchange arbitrage works best when pairing Bitget positions with Binance or OKX due to liquidity differences and timing variations in funding calculations."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SHIB's high volatility can result in significant mark-to-market losses that exceed funding rate gains, requiring tight position sizing and stop-loss protocols. Bitget's relatively newer status means lower institutional participation, creating higher funding rate volatility but also increased execution risk during market stress. The exchange's customer support inconsistencies can impact urgent position management needs during extreme market conditions. Traders should maintain positions below 10x leverage and implement automatic profit-taking at 0.15% funding rates to manage tail risks effectively."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are SHIB/USDT funding rates calculated on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget calculates SHIB/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The funding fee exchange occurs automatically at these settlement times based on your open position size."},{"question":"What are typical SHIB funding rates on Bitget compared to other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget's SHIB funding rates often run 0.01-0.05% higher than major exchanges like Binance during bullish meme coin cycles due to higher retail participation. During neutral periods, rates typically align within 0.02% across exchanges."},{"question":"Can I use Bitget's copy trading for funding rate strategies on SHIB?","answer":"While Bitget's copy trading supports SHIB perpetuals, most copy traders focus on directional strategies rather than funding rate arbitrage. Manual execution is recommended for funding rate capture as timing and position management are critical for success."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate cap for SHIB on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget caps SHIB/USDT funding rates at +/-0.375% per 8-hour period to prevent extreme funding costs during high volatility events. This cap helps protect both long and short position holders from excessive funding payments."}]}]
